cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of depth completion using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning adaptive convolutional kernel sizes and the number of iterations for propagation, which is a form of architecture search (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of soft weighting parameters to dynamically assign computational resources, which is related to resource allocation and optimization (cs.AI, cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a gated network to handle noisy or inaccurate data, which is a common technique in neural network training (cs.NE).
